text:
Deep fried Angoli fish head braised with bittergourd in bean sauce - star highlight of dinner
Meaty fish head, chewy and soft, and crunchy... The chef is a master at combining flavours and textures
Perfect with steaming hot white rice
Fried fish sang min... Full of flavours and textures, very satisfying
Fish slice bee hoon soup... Thick slices of fish no bone

Hidden gem here in this area, for the price of $4.50 including rice their fried fish soup is very different from other stores where they don't add the fish into the soup they serve it in another bowl to keep the fish fresh and crispy. Highly recommend it üëç
Kopitiam serves very nice muah chee! With original peanuts chunks or you can mix with peanut and black sesame.

Many new & existing stalls offering decent tasty fares @ higher pricing after reno..
Avoid peak hours as no available tables for dining üòÅ

My usual Vermicelli and fish fillet.
Used to be $1.80 and just paid $2.40.
That's 33% increased
